{"cursor":"13731","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox university |name = 'Goodman School of Business' |image = |established\n= 1990 |type = Public School of business |undergrad = 2,200 |postgrad = 233\n[http://www.brocku.ca/instanalysis/brockfacts/2008/library.html Brock\nUniversity, Department of Institutional Planning and Analysis] |dean = Dr.\nDon A. Cyr |campus = |city = St. Catharines |province = ON |country = Canada\n|former_names = Faculty of Business |affiliations = AACSB, EFMD, BGS |website =\n[http://brocku.ca/business/]\n|}}\n\nThe 'Goodman School of Business' ('Goodman') is the business school of Brock\nUniversity in St. Catharines, Ontario, Canada. The business school offers\nprograms at both the undergraduate and graduate level of study.\n\nThe Goodman School of Business is one of five Canadian business schools to\nattain accreditation by the AACSB as well as membership in Beta Gamma\nSigma. [http://www.betagammasigma.org/chapterlist.htm Beta Gamma\nSigma]\n\nOn October 12, 2012 Brock announced that its Faculty of Business was being\nrenamed as the Goodman School of Business. The School is named after the family\nof Ned Goodman, the businessman and investment expert, who provided the\nUniversity with a gift to the school. [http://brocku.ca/news/20741]\n","linknr":273,"url":"Brock_Faculty_of_Business","recorded":1374539421,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Goodman_School_of_Business&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Goodman_School_of_Business&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Goodman_School_of_Business","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTran